      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>J.T. Gregory (1946?1960) served as curator in the division of vertebrate paleontology from 1946-1960. While much of his time was spent heading up renovations to the exhibits and buildings, he also led several expeditions, making substantial collections from New Mexico, Oklahoma and Wyoming.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>This is a small selection of archives, mainly field notes and specimen lists.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
